This after Malawi last week, passed the IMF test as the fund's Executive Board of Directors approved resources to support reconstruction efforts after the devastating Cyclone Idai. 

The board also met to complete the second and third reviews of the three-year Extended Credit Facility, ECF, programme with Malawi, an arrangement which is worth $112-million. George Mhango filed this report from Blantyre, Malawi… --ChannelAfrica--